            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Layer the <strong>drained</strong> <strong>sliced potatoes</strong> on top, dot them with a few knobs of <strong>butter</strong> and sprinkle with<strong> </strong>the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>chopped thyme</strong></p><p>Put the dish on a baking tray in the oven and cook for 25-30 min or until the potatoes are brown and crispy – this is your <strong>Lancashire-style lamb hotpot</strong></p><p>Once the Lancashire-style lamb hotpot is done, remove it from the oven and set aside to cool a little (this helps the flavours to develop and makes it easier to serve!)</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/956.-step-6-x200.jpg",
